What you need to know:  There is no doubt that corruption in Kenya is widespread and deep-rooted in the body public.It has become a way of life, embraced by the citizens and their leaders. Those among us who engage in corruption love it while those who don’t engage in the vice tolerate it.This is evident in the “National Ethics and Corruption Survey 2021” report, which indicated that over half of Kenyans do nothing at the individual level to support anti-corruption initiatives.